		<div id="comment_body_64882099"><p>I mainly use a nice RPN calculator on my phone. It's vastly superior to regular infix calculators, especially when you know how to manipulate the stack and set it to show several values.</p><p>I took a look because I never really thought about the fact that it lacks a normal clear button. It has a backspace, which clears the last typed character, or if the top-of-stack is a calculation result, sets the whole register to zero (never realized that feature). It also has a clear stack (similar to AC), and a "drop" to<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64882099">

</div>
